<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.mh" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_sbhd0">
	HOME DEPARTMENT
</major-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.1" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.1" nospeaker="true" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn0">
	Chief Constables (Eligibility)
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/744" speakername="Peter Bottomley" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn0">
	<p pid=".795W.2/1" qnum="4793">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department when military officers became ineligible for appointment as chief constables; and by what means.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4793.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew0">
	<p pid=".795W.3/1">The appointment of a chief constable is a matter for decision by the appropriate police authority, subject to the approval of the Secretary of State. In making an appointment, a police authority will want to be fully satisfied that the individual selected has the necessary abilities and experience to lead an effective and efficient police force. Since the 1960s, regulations under the Police Act 1964 have included a requirement that no person may be appointed as a chief constable without prior experience in a supervisory police rank. Since 1979 that requirement has been for an appointee to have had at least two years' experience in the rank of superintendent or in a higher rank.</p>
	<p pid=".795W.3/2">Current guidance to police authorities indicates that appointment to all chief officer ranks in forces will only receive approval from the Secretary of State where the individual has attended the strategic command course for senior police officers. This guidance reflects a recommendation by the Home Affairs Committee (Third Report, Session 1988&ndash;89) that this should be a compulsory requirement for all applicants for posts at chief officer rank.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.4" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.4" nospeaker="true" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn1">
	Antisocial Behaviour Orders
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.5" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/889" speakername="Caroline Flint" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn1">
	<p pid=".795W.5/1" qnum="4982">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what proportion of antisocial behaviour orders have been breached by individuals where that breach led to a custodial sentence.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.6" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.4982.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.6" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew1">
	<p pid=".795W.6/1">Provisional data taken from the Home Office court proceedings database up to December 2000 show that 48 per cent. of offenders who have breached antisocial behaviour orders have been given a custodial sentence for the breach.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.7" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.7" nospeaker="true" inserted-heading="true" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn2">
	Antisocial Behaviour Orders
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.8" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.8" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1055" speakername="Tim Loughton" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn2">
	<p pid=".795W.8/1" qnum="5937">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department how many antisocial behaviour orders have been issued in Sussex; and how many have led to subsequent court proceedings.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.9" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5937.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.795W.9" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="795W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew2">
	<p pid=".795W.9/1">Available data show that up to <phrase class="date" code="2001-03-31">31 March 2001</phrase> four antisocial behaviour orders (ASBOs) have been issued within the Sussex area.</p>
	<p pid=".795W.9/2">Provisional data taken from the Home Office court proceedings database show that up to December 2000 two persons within the Sussex police force area have been proceeded against for the criminal offence of breaching an ASBO.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.0" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn3">
	Recorded Crime (North Oxfordshire)
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.1" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/777" speakername="David Cameron" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn3">
	<p pid=".796W.1/1" qnum="5757">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what the level of recorded crime was in the North Oxfordshire area of the Thames Valley in each year from 1996 to 2000.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5757.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew3">
	<p pid=".796W.2/1">Overall numbers of recorded crimes at basic command unit (BCU) level are not collected centrally. Total numbers for certain categories of recorded crime have been collected centrally at BCU level since <phrase class="date" code="1999-04-01">1 April 1999</phrase>. The information for the North Oxfordshire BCU is as follows:</p>
