<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.3" nospeaker="true" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn4">
	Police (Working Conditions)
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.4" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/982" speakername="Simon Hughes" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn4">
	<p pid=".796W.4/1" qnum="5203">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what representations he has received concerning the working conditions of police inspectors and chief inspectors; what measures he plans to introduce to address the concerns raised; and if he will make a statement.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.5" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5203.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew4">
	<p pid=".796W.5/1" class="holdinganswer">holding answer <phrase class="date" code="2001-07-19">19 July 2001</phrase></p>
	<p pid=".796W.5/2">The inspectors central committee wrote to my predecessor, my right hon. Friend <phrase class="honfriend" id="uk.org.publicwhip/member/801" name="Charles Clarke">the Member for Norwich, South (Mr. Clarke)</phrase> in March regarding the effects of changes made in 1994 to the working conditions for inspecting ranks.</p>
	<p pid=".796W.5/3">Decisions relating to the number of officers and the rank in which they are employed, together with assessing and addressing health and safety issues, are matters for chief officers.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.6" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.6" nospeaker="true" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn5">
	Prisons
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.7" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.7" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1291" speakername="Andrew Turner" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn5">
	<p pid=".796W.7/1" qnum="5501">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what records he keeps of the number of prisoners with psychiatric problems in each prison.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.8" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5501.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.8" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/980" speakername="Beverley Hughes" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew5">
	<p pid=".796W.8/1">All Prison Service establishments are required to submit monthly statistical returns on a range of health care activity to the prison health policy unit. The information provided includes the total number of prisoners receiving treatment in prison for mental health reasons, either as out-patients or in the health care centre; and national health service activity, including the numbers of prisoners who had been seen by a psychiatrist, and who had been transferred to hospital or who were awaiting such a transfer.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.9" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.9" nospeaker="true" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn6">
	Firearms
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.10" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.796W.10" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1317" speakername="Ann Widdecombe" colnum="796W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn6">
	<p pid=".796W.10/1" qnum="5787">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what estimates he has made of the number of illegally held firearms in the United Kingdom; and if he will make a statement.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.797W.0" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5787.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.797W.0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="797W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew6">
	<p pid=".797W.0/1">There is no reliable means of estimating the number of illegally held firearms in the United Kingdom.</p>
	<p pid=".797W.0/2">The existence of any illegal firearms is of great concern to the Government and we are fully committed to supporting the police and other law enforcement agencies in their efforts to combat the illegal possession and criminal use of firearms.</p>
	<p pid=".797W.0/3">The use of firearms in crime is small in relation both to overall national crime figures (0.1 per cent.) and to other comparable countries. We are liaising closely with the police to establish the source of illegal weapons. There is no evidence at present of organised and large-scale smuggling; nor does there appear to be a single main source of firearms.</p>
	<p pid=".797W.0/4">Armed crime cannot be tackled in isolation from other criminal activities, in particular drug trafficking and robbery. Tackling these crimes is one of the Government's highest priorities.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.0" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="798W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn7">
	Police Duties
</minor-heading>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.1" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.q0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.q0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/710" speakername="Norman Baker" colnum="798W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn7">
	<p pid=".798W.1/1" qnum="5484">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what information is available to him to determine the percentage of a police constable's time spent on average <i>(a) </i>on patrol, <i>(b)</i> undertaking duties within a police establishment, <i>(c) </i>off sick, <i>(d) </i>on leave and <i>(e) </i>otherwise engaged, for the last year for which figures are available.</p>
</ques>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.r0" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5484.r0" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/851" speakername="John Denham" colnum="798W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_spnew7">
	<p pid=".798W.2/1" class="holdinganswer">holding answer <phrase class="date" code="2001-07-20">20 July 2001</phrase></p>
	<p pid=".798W.2/2">I wrote to the hon. Member on <phrase class="date" code="2001-09-20">20 September</phrase> and placed a copy of my letter in the Library.</p>
</reply>

<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5691.h" matchtype="oldwransgid"/>
<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.5691.h" oldstyleid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2001-10-04.798W.3" nospeaker="true" colnum="798W"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200102/cmhansrd/vo011004/text/11004w01.htm#11004w01.html_wqn8">
	Police (Manpower Targets)
</minor-heading>

